Russian Equity Movers: Polyus Gold, Razgulay, Rosneft Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-08T16:04:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/russian-equity-movers-polymetal-polyus-gold-razgulay-rosneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  retreated
5.5 percent to 1,499.79 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, its
biggest drop since May 2010. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
sank 7.8 percent to 1,657.77  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX), the country’s largest gold
producer, rose for the third day, adding 0.1 percent to 1,652.3
rubles, as the metal advanced to a record.  OAO Razgulay (GRAZ RX), a Russian sugar producer, slid by
the most in more than two years as the price of the sweetener
dropped. The company’s shares lost 10.2 percent to 39.02 rubles,
the biggest loss since May 2009.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),  Russia ’s largest oil producer,
retreated by the most in more than a year as crude slumped in
 New York  after  Standard & Poor’s  lowered the U.S. credit rating.
The shares dropped 5.5 percent to 207.29 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
